('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Stonehenge is a prehistoric monument in Wiltshire whose exact purpose still remains a mystery to archaeologists'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The London Underground is the oldest subway system in the world and started operating in eighteen sixty three'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Winston Churchill led the United Kingdom through the most difficult years of the Second World War'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Edinburgh is the capital of Scotland and hosts the largest arts festival in the world every August'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The British Parliament is divided into two chambers the House of Commons and the House of Lords'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Charles Darwin developed the theory of evolution after travelling around the world on a ship called Beagle'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Tower of London has served as a royal palace a prison and a treasury throughout its long history'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Agatha Christie is the best selling novelist of all time with her famous detective Hercule Poirot'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Magna Carta was signed in twelve fifteen and became a symbol of rights and liberties in England'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Oxford and Cambridge are two of the oldest and most prestigious universities in the English speaking world'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Lake District in northern England inspired many Romantic poets like William Wordsworth and Samuel Coleridge'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Alexander Fleming accidentally discovered penicillin in his laboratory and saved millions of human lives'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Sherlock Holmes is the fictional detective created by Arthur Conan Doyle who lives at Baker Street'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Thames is the most important river in England and flows through the centre of London city'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'J K Rowling wrote the Harry Potter series in Edinburgh cafes while she was a single mother'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Scottish Highlands offer some of the most beautiful and dramatic natural landscapes in Great Britain'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Buckingham Palace has been the official London residence of British monarchs since the year eighteen thirty seven'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Romeo and Juliet tells the tragic story of two young lovers from rival families in the city of Verona'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Beatles were formed in Liverpool and their members were John Paul George and Ringo Starr'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Emily Bronte wrote Wuthering Heights a novel about passion and revenge set in the Yorkshire moors'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The English breakfast traditionally includes eggs bacon sausages beans mushrooms tomatoes and toast with tea'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Christopher Wren designed Saint Paul Cathedral after the Great Fire of London destroyed most of the city'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Lewis Carroll wrote Alice in Wonderland while working as a mathematics teacher at Oxford University'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Roman Empire occupied Britain for nearly four hundred years and left behind roads walls and cities'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Robin Hood is a legendary hero who supposedly lived in Sherwood Forest stealing from the rich and giving to the poor'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Prime Meridian passes through Greenwich in London and divides the world into east and west hemispheres'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'King Arthur is a legendary British king whose stories are linked to the knights of the Round Table'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Shakespeare wrote thirty seven plays including tragedies comedies and historical dramas during his lifetime'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'The Union Jack combines the crosses of Saint George Saint Andrew and Saint Patrick in one single flag'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Fish and chips became the traditional takeaway meal in Britain during the nineteenth century near working class towns');
INSERT INTO detective_sentences (subject_id, level, grades, sentence) VALUES
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Adam Smith published The Wealth of Nations and laid the foundations of modern economic and market theory'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'John Locke argued that government legitimacy derives from the consent of the governed and natural rights'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Glorious Revolution of sixteen eighty eight established constitutional monarchy as the basis of British government'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'George Orwell wrote Nineteen Eighty Four as a warning against totalitarianism and the dangers of mass surveillance'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Brexit referendum in twenty sixteen marked a historical turning point in relations between Britain and Europe'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Virginia Woolf revolutionised modernist literature with her stream of consciousness technique in novels like Mrs Dalloway'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Bank of England was founded in sixteen ninety four and remains one of the oldest central banks in existence'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Thomas Hobbes defended in Leviathan that absolute sovereignty was necessary to prevent the state of nature'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The British Welfare State was established after the Second World War following the Beveridge Report recommendations'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'James Joyce wrote Ulysses in Paris as a modernist masterpiece that revolutionised the novel as a literary form'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Margaret Thatcher became the first female Prime Minister and implemented economic policies known as Thatcherism'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'T S Eliot wrote The Waste Land capturing the sense of spiritual desolation after the First World War'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Enlightenment period produced philosophers such as David Hume who questioned the foundations of human knowledge'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'John Maynard Keynes developed economic theories advocating government intervention during times of financial crisis'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Aldous Huxley imagined in Brave New World a dystopian society controlled through pleasure and genetic engineering'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Commonwealth of Nations is an association of fifty six countries most of them former British colonies'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Oscar Wilde satirised Victorian society in plays like The Importance of Being Earnest and novels about moral decay'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Suffragette movement fought for decades until women finally achieved the right to vote in nineteen eighteen'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Samuel Beckett wrote Waiting for Godot as an absurdist play questioning the meaning of human existence itself'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The British Royal Family retains a ceremonial role despite the country being a constitutional parliamentary democracy'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Alan Turing cracked the Enigma code during the war and later founded the principles of modern computer science'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Romantic movement in British literature celebrated nature emotion and the individual imagination over cold reason'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Graham Greene explored themes of faith betrayal and moral ambiguity in novels like The Power and the Glory'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Magna Carta established for the first time that even the king must be subject to the rule of law'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'William Blake combined poetry and visual art in his illuminated books such as Songs of Innocence and Experience'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Battle of Trafalgar secured British naval supremacy for over a century under the command of Admiral Nelson'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Kazuo Ishiguro won the Nobel Prize in Literature for novels exploring memory identity and historical trauma'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The British Museum in London contains millions of artefacts representing cultures from all around the world'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Doris Lessing examined gender politics and colonialism in novels set in Africa and post war London'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Financial Crisis of two thousand eight began with the collapse of major American and British banking institutions'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Ian McEwan explores moral dilemmas and human relationships in contemporary novels such as Atonement and Enduring Love'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The House of Lords is the upper chamber of the British Parliament and includes both hereditary and life peers'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Bertrand Russell was a philosopher mathematician and social activist who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in nineteen fifty'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Salman Rushdie explored postcolonial themes in Midnight Children which won the Booker Prize in nineteen eighty one'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The National Health Service provides free healthcare to all British citizens and is funded through general taxation'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'William Golding wrote Lord of the Flies as a dark allegory about human nature and the fragility of civilisation'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'The Declaration of Human Rights was largely influenced by British philosophical traditions concerning liberty and justice'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Joseph Conrad wrote Heart of Darkness based on his experiences navigating rivers during the colonial era'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Stephen Hawking revolutionised our understanding of black holes and wrote popular books about the nature of time and space'),
('ingles', 'bachillerato', '{2}', 'Harold Pinter developed a theatrical style characterised by ambiguous dialogue pauses and underlying menace on stage');
INSERT INTO detective_sentences (subject_id, level, grades, sentence) VALUES
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Victor Hugo a écrit Les Misérables un roman qui dénonce les injustices sociales de la France du dix-neuvième siècle'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La Révolution française a commencé en mil sept cent quatre-vingt-neuf avec la prise de la Bastille'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Napoléon Bonaparte est devenu empereur des Français et a conquis une grande partie de l''Europe continentale'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La tour Eiffel a été construite pour l''Exposition universelle de mil huit cent quatre-vingt-neuf à Paris'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Louvre est le musée le plus visité du monde et abrite la célèbre peinture de la Joconde'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Jeanne d''Arc est une héroïne française qui a combattu les Anglais pendant la guerre de Cent Ans'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Alexandre Dumas a écrit Les Trois Mousquetaires un roman d''aventures très populaire dans le monde entier'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La Déclaration des droits de l''homme et du citoyen a été adoptée pendant la Révolution française'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Molière est considéré comme le plus grand auteur de comédies de la littérature française classique'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le château de Versailles a été construit par le roi Louis quatorze et il représente le pouvoir absolu'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Jules Verne a imaginé des voyages extraordinaires dans ses romans comme Vingt mille lieues sous les mers'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le croissant et la baguette sont deux symboles gastronomiques de la culture française reconnus partout dans le monde'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Charles de Gaulle a dirigé la Résistance française pendant la Seconde Guerre mondiale depuis Londres'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La cathédrale Notre-Dame de Paris a été gravement endommagée par un incendie au mois d''avril deux mille dix-neuf'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Claude Monet est le fondateur du mouvement impressionniste et il a peint de nombreux tableaux de son jardin à Giverny'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Petit Prince est un conte philosophique écrit par Antoine de Saint-Exupéry pendant son exil aux États-Unis'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La devise de la République française est liberté égalité fraternité et elle date de la Révolution'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Jean de La Fontaine a composé des fables qui utilisent des animaux pour critiquer la société de son époque'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Moulin Rouge est un cabaret mythique situé dans le quartier de Montmartre au nord de Paris'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Marie Curie a reçu deux prix Nobel pour ses recherches sur la radioactivité des éléments chimiques'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Tour de France est la course cycliste la plus célèbre du monde et se déroule au mois de juillet'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Louis Pasteur a découvert le vaccin contre la rage et a révolutionné la médecine moderne avec ses recherches'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La Marseillaise est l''hymne national français composé pendant la Révolution par Claude Joseph Rouget de Lisle'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Gustave Flaubert a écrit Madame Bovary un roman réaliste qui a provoqué un scandale à sa publication'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Mont Saint-Michel est une île rocheuse de Normandie célèbre pour son abbaye médiévale et ses marées'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Honoré de Balzac a écrit La Comédie humaine une série de romans qui décrivent la société française du dix-neuvième siècle'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La Francophonie regroupe les pays où le français est parlé officiellement ou comme langue de culture importante'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Édith Piaf est une chanteuse française célèbre pour des titres comme La vie en rose et Non je ne regrette rien'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le festival de Cannes est l''un des festivals de cinéma les plus prestigieux du monde et a lieu chaque année en mai'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Auguste Rodin est un sculpteur français célèbre pour des œuvres comme Le Penseur et Le Baiser'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La galette des rois est une tradition française que l''on mange au mois de janvier pour célébrer l''Épiphanie'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Coco Chanel a révolutionné la mode féminine en créant des vêtements élégants et confortables pour les femmes modernes'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Mont Blanc est la plus haute montagne d''Europe occidentale et se trouve à la frontière entre la France et l''Italie'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Jean-Paul Sartre est un philosophe existentialiste qui a refusé le prix Nobel de littérature en mil neuf cent soixante-quatre'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Les frères Lumière ont inventé le cinématographe et ont organisé la première projection publique de films à Paris'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Le Quartier latin est un quartier historique de Paris où se trouvent la Sorbonne et de nombreuses autres universités'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'Édouard Manet est considéré comme un précurseur de l''impressionnisme avec des tableaux comme Le déjeuner sur l''herbe'),
('frances', 'bachillerato', '{1}', 'La Provence est une région du sud de la France célèbre pour ses champs de lavande et sa cuisine méditerranéenne'),
